[
    {
        "index": 1,
        "start_time": 7470,
        "end_time": 12415,
        "text": "In 1965, 17-year-old high school student,\nRandy Gardner"
    },
    {
        "index": 2,
        "start_time": 12415,
        "end_time": 16042,
        "text": "stayed award for 264 hours."
    },
    {
        "index": 3,
        "start_time": 16042,
        "end_time": 20060,
        "text": "That&#39;s 11 days to see how\nhe&#39;d cope without sleep."
    },
    {
        "index": 4,
        "start_time": 20060,
        "end_time": 23241,
        "text": "On the second day, \nhis eyes stopped focusing."
    },
    {
        "index": 5,
        "start_time": 23241,
        "end_time": 27350,
        "text": "Next, he lost the ability\nto identify objects by touch."
    },
    {
        "index": 6,
        "start_time": 27350,
        "end_time": 30917,
        "text": "By day three, Gardner was moody\nand uncoordinated."
    },
    {
        "index": 7,
        "start_time": 30917,
        "end_time": 33806,
        "text": "At the end of the experiment,\nhe was struggling to concentrate,"
    },
    {
        "index": 8,
        "start_time": 33806,
        "end_time": 35607,
        "text": "had trouble with short-term memory,"
    },
    {
        "index": 9,
        "start_time": 35607,
        "end_time": 37107,
        "text": "became paranoid,"
    },
    {
        "index": 10,
        "start_time": 37107,
        "end_time": 39011,
        "text": "and started hallucinating."
    },
    {
        "index": 11,
        "start_time": 39011,
        "end_time": 41741,
        "text": "Although Gardner recovered without\nlong-term psychological"
    },
    {
        "index": 12,
        "start_time": 41741,
        "end_time": 43409,
        "text": "or physical damage,"
    },
    {
        "index": 13,
        "start_time": 43409,
        "end_time": 47100,
        "text": "for others, losing shuteye can result\nin hormonal imbalance,"
    },
    {
        "index": 14,
        "start_time": 47100,
        "end_time": 48192,
        "text": "illness,"
    },
    {
        "index": 15,
        "start_time": 48192,
        "end_time": 50601,
        "text": "and, in extreme cases, death."
    },
    {
        "index": 16,
        "start_time": 50601,
        "end_time": 55027,
        "text": "We&#39;re only beginning to understand\nwhy we sleep to begin with,"
    },
    {
        "index": 17,
        "start_time": 55027,
        "end_time": 56965,
        "text": "but we do know it&#39;s essential."
    },
    {
        "index": 18,
        "start_time": 56965,
        "end_time": 59916,
        "text": "Adults need seven to eight hours\nof sleep a night,"
    },
    {
        "index": 19,
        "start_time": 59916,
        "end_time": 62170,
        "text": "and adolescents need about ten."
    },
    {
        "index": 20,
        "start_time": 62170,
        "end_time": 64679,
        "text": "We grow sleepy due to signals\nfrom our body"
    },
    {
        "index": 21,
        "start_time": 64679,
        "end_time": 66986,
        "text": "telling our brain we are tired,"
    },
    {
        "index": 22,
        "start_time": 66986,
        "end_time": 70512,
        "text": "and signals from the environment\ntelling us it&#39;s dark outside."
    },
    {
        "index": 23,
        "start_time": 70512,
        "end_time": 72881,
        "text": "The rise in sleep-inducing chemicals,"
    },
    {
        "index": 24,
        "start_time": 72881,
        "end_time": 75136,
        "text": "like adenosine and melatonin,"
    },
    {
        "index": 25,
        "start_time": 75136,
        "end_time": 78348,
        "text": "send us into a light doze \nthat grows deeper,"
    },
    {
        "index": 26,
        "start_time": 78348,
        "end_time": 80951,
        "text": "making our breathing \nand heart rate slow down"
    },
    {
        "index": 27,
        "start_time": 80951,
        "end_time": 83577,
        "text": "and our muscles relax."
    },
    {
        "index": 28,
        "start_time": 83577,
        "end_time": 87075,
        "text": "This non-REM sleep is when DNA is repaired"
    },
    {
        "index": 29,
        "start_time": 87075,
        "end_time": 90481,
        "text": "and our bodies replenish themselves\nfor the day ahead."
    },
    {
        "index": 30,
        "start_time": 90481,
        "end_time": 92061,
        "text": "In the United States,"
    },
    {
        "index": 31,
        "start_time": 92061,
        "end_time": 96681,
        "text": "it&#39;s estimated that 30% of adults\nand 66% of adolescents"
    },
    {
        "index": 32,
        "start_time": 96681,
        "end_time": 99124,
        "text": "are regularly sleep-deprived."
    },
    {
        "index": 33,
        "start_time": 99124,
        "end_time": 101503,
        "text": "This isn&#39;t just a minor inconvenience."
    },
    {
        "index": 34,
        "start_time": 101503,
        "end_time": 104841,
        "text": "Staying awake can cause \nserious bodily harm."
    },
    {
        "index": 35,
        "start_time": 104841,
        "end_time": 106159,
        "text": "When we lose sleep,"
    },
    {
        "index": 36,
        "start_time": 106159,
        "end_time": 107004,
        "text": "learning,"
    },
    {
        "index": 37,
        "start_time": 107004,
        "end_time": 107828,
        "text": "memory,"
    },
    {
        "index": 38,
        "start_time": 107828,
        "end_time": 108538,
        "text": "mood,"
    },
    {
        "index": 39,
        "start_time": 108538,
        "end_time": 110783,
        "text": "and reaction time are affected."
    },
    {
        "index": 40,
        "start_time": 110783,
        "end_time": 113385,
        "text": "Sleeplessness may also cause inflammation,"
    },
    {
        "index": 41,
        "start_time": 113385,
        "end_time": 114607,
        "text": "halluciations,"
    },
    {
        "index": 42,
        "start_time": 114607,
        "end_time": 115957,
        "text": "high blood pressure,"
    },
    {
        "index": 43,
        "start_time": 115957,
        "end_time": 120424,
        "text": "and it&#39;s even been linked\nto diabetes and obesity."
    },
    {
        "index": 44,
        "start_time": 120424,
        "end_time": 123906,
        "text": "In 2014, a devoted soccer fan died"
    },
    {
        "index": 45,
        "start_time": 123906,
        "end_time": 128091,
        "text": "after staying awake for 48 hours \nto watch the World Cup."
    },
    {
        "index": 46,
        "start_time": 128091,
        "end_time": 130822,
        "text": "While his untimely death \nwas due to a stroke,"
    },
    {
        "index": 47,
        "start_time": 130822,
        "end_time": 134614,
        "text": "studies show that chronically sleeping\nfewer than six hours a night"
    },
    {
        "index": 48,
        "start_time": 134614,
        "end_time": 138598,
        "text": "increases stroke risk \nby four and half times"
    },
    {
        "index": 49,
        "start_time": 138598,
        "end_time": 142936,
        "text": "compared to those getting a consistent\nseven to eight hours of shuteye."
    },
    {
        "index": 50,
        "start_time": 142936,
        "end_time": 147556,
        "text": "For a handful of people on the planet who\ncarry a rare inherited genetic mutation,"
    },
    {
        "index": 51,
        "start_time": 147556,
        "end_time": 150063,
        "text": "sleeplessness is a daily reality."
    },
    {
        "index": 52,
        "start_time": 150063,
        "end_time": 154136,
        "text": "This condition, \nknown as Fatal Familial Insomnia,"
    },
    {
        "index": 53,
        "start_time": 154136,
        "end_time": 157609,
        "text": "places the body in a nightmarish \nstate of wakefulness,"
    },
    {
        "index": 54,
        "start_time": 157609,
        "end_time": 160915,
        "text": "forbidding it from entering \nthe sanctuary of sleep."
    },
    {
        "index": 55,
        "start_time": 160915,
        "end_time": 162746,
        "text": "Within months or years,"
    },
    {
        "index": 56,
        "start_time": 162746,
        "end_time": 167494,
        "text": "this progressively worsening condition\nleads to dementia and death."
    },
    {
        "index": 57,
        "start_time": 167494,
        "end_time": 171325,
        "text": "How can sleep deprivation\ncause such immense suffering?"
    },
    {
        "index": 58,
        "start_time": 171325,
        "end_time": 175308,
        "text": "Scientists think the answer lies\nwith the accumulation of waste prducts"
    },
    {
        "index": 59,
        "start_time": 175308,
        "end_time": 176915,
        "text": "in the brain."
    },
    {
        "index": 60,
        "start_time": 176915,
        "end_time": 178482,
        "text": "During our waking hours,"
    },
    {
        "index": 61,
        "start_time": 178482,
        "end_time": 181724,
        "text": "our cells are busy using up\nour day&#39;s energy sources,"
    },
    {
        "index": 62,
        "start_time": 181724,
        "end_time": 184385,
        "text": "which get broken down \ninto various byproducts,"
    },
    {
        "index": 63,
        "start_time": 184385,
        "end_time": 186673,
        "text": "including adenosine."
    },
    {
        "index": 64,
        "start_time": 186673,
        "end_time": 188457,
        "text": "As adenosine builds up,"
    },
    {
        "index": 65,
        "start_time": 188457,
        "end_time": 192913,
        "text": "it increases the urge to sleep,\nalso known as sleep pressure."
    },
    {
        "index": 66,
        "start_time": 192913,
        "end_time": 198273,
        "text": "In fact, caffeine works by blocking\nadenosine&#39;s receptor pathways."
    },
    {
        "index": 67,
        "start_time": 198273,
        "end_time": 200969,
        "text": "Other waste products \nalso build up in the brain,"
    },
    {
        "index": 68,
        "start_time": 200969,
        "end_time": 204986,
        "text": "and if they&#39;re not cleared away,\nthey collectively overload the brain"
    },
    {
        "index": 69,
        "start_time": 204986,
        "end_time": 209536,
        "text": "and are thought to lead to the many\nnegative symptoms of sleep deprivation."
    },
    {
        "index": 70,
        "start_time": 209536,
        "end_time": 213938,
        "text": "So, what&#39;s happening in our brain\nwhen we sleep to prevent this?"
    },
    {
        "index": 71,
        "start_time": 213938,
        "end_time": 217246,
        "text": "Scientists found something called\nthe glymphatic system,"
    },
    {
        "index": 72,
        "start_time": 217246,
        "end_time": 220355,
        "text": "a clean-up mechanism \nthat removes this buildup"
    },
    {
        "index": 73,
        "start_time": 220355,
        "end_time": 223219,
        "text": "and is much more active when we&#39;re asleep."
    },
    {
        "index": 74,
        "start_time": 223219,
        "end_time": 228645,
        "text": "It works by using cerebrospinal fluid\nto flush away toxic byproducts"
    },
    {
        "index": 75,
        "start_time": 228645,
        "end_time": 230997,
        "text": "that accumulate between cells."
    },
    {
        "index": 76,
        "start_time": 230997,
        "end_time": 234970,
        "text": "Lymphatic vessels, \nwhich serve as pathways for immune cells,"
    },
    {
        "index": 77,
        "start_time": 234970,
        "end_time": 237866,
        "text": "have recently been discovered \nin the brain,"
    },
    {
        "index": 78,
        "start_time": 237866,
        "end_time": 243951,
        "text": "and they may also play a role in clearing\nout the brain&#39;s daily waste products."
    },
    {
        "index": 79,
        "start_time": 243951,
        "end_time": 248966,
        "text": "While scientists continue exploring\nthe restorative mechanisms behind sleep,"
    },
    {
        "index": 80,
        "start_time": 248966,
        "end_time": 253202,
        "text": "we can be sure that slipping \ninto slumber is a necessity"
    },
    {
        "index": 81,
        "start_time": 253202,
        "end_time": 256930,
        "text": "if we want to maintain our health\nand our sanity."
    }
]